Therefore, it is advised that you first ensure that your parent fish does have the mutation in their germ line. To do this, first take a cohort of embryos, extract their DNA and sequence it, or do a headloop PCR, to check. This adds time to an already laborious technique.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9qrpl","text":"The Fish Facility does not currently give you enough time to screen the animals before they are put into the nursery.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"105ql","text":"The first lab to use this technique have grown these fish to adulthood and bred them with no issues - that has not been achieved at UCL though so it is likely there will be a drop off in survival","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3td6t","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7btcp","text":"It would be a good idea to try this first with raising a new generation of a line that we know doesn’t have any problems with viability in the nursery, just to check that the tail clipping doesn’t introduce any additional mortality in our system. {"blocks":[{"key":"4tvad","text":"Fish need to be at least 48 hours post fertilisation","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fhpc0","text":"Use a Pasteur pipette to add the fish to the 1X tricane solution and wait for it to stop moving. Just after the blood vessel turns back on itself, there is a small pigment gap.
